<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007-04-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Public health preparedness: a systems‐level approach</TITLE><BODY>Public health and emergency preparedness have become central concepts in the current restructuring of various regional‐, national‐ and global‐level public health and emergency management agencies and systems. In this article, a glossary of the most important terms and concepts currently pertaining to public health preparedness is provided with a focus on systems‐level and organisational issues.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>